Before completion, it is backed up (the isilon is backed up to AWS). At completion, it is preserved, and will be recoverable via the deletion marker UI.

We decided to use the complete state to trigger preservation, as initially proposed in this ticket.

figgy.title: Redesign the preservation status indicators on the resource show page

comments.body: Still to determine: What happens visually when you click the "report" button?

The consensus is that, at a minimum, there will be some system notification to the user that the issue was reported. This may be a flash alert or animation that confirms it was successfully reported (or not). Th state of which files have been reported would not be saved on the server. 

Note: If state is not saved, it could be hard for a user to know which issues have been reported or not if there are a lot of errors in the Filemanager interface. We could mitigate this confusion by storing ids that have been reported locally on the client, saving the state at least for the duration of the user's session or until they clear their cookies.
